# ROS2 LiDAR Corridor Navigation (Reactive)

Reactive corridor/maze navigation in **ROS2** using only **2D LiDAR (/scan)**.
No SLAM, no Nav2, no global planner.

## Demo
- Video: https://drive.google.com/file/d/12R3s0P7lfGvG4RxDxmDoib1ueH8cu0Jc/view?usp=sharing
- Key behavior: go straight when clear, avoid frontal obstacles by turning toward the more open side.

## Repository structure
maze_runner/
├─ launch/
│ └─ maze_runner.launch.py
├─ maze_runner/
│ ├─ init.py
│ └─ wall_follower.py
├─ resource/
├─ package.xml
├─ setup.py
└─ setup.cfg


## Topics
**Subscribed**
- `/scan` (`sensor_msgs/LaserScan`)

**Published**
- `/cmd_vel` (`geometry_msgs/Twist`)

## How it works (high level)
1. Drive straight by default  
2. If obstacle in front (`front < front_stop`): turn toward the more open diagonal (LF vs RF)  
3. If side wall is very close: steer away slightly  

All decisions are based on LiDAR sector distances.

## Run
Build from a ROS2 workspace:

```bash
cd ~/ros2_ws
colcon build --symlink-install
source install/setup.bash
ros2 launch maze_runner maze_runner.launch.py
